eNCA's Heidi Giokos reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Government has promised Soweto residents that their electricity woes will soon be a thing of the past. Gauteng Premier, Panyaza Lesufi engaged with residents on Sunday. The area owes Eskom almost R5-billion in unpaid bills, a debt Lesufi wants written off. But is this possible amid the country's worsening electricity crisis? eNCA reporter, Heidi Giokos was there and filed this report in the video above.